### What this plan does NOT do

- Create new node kinds or edge types
- Enrich SY nodes (1:many problem, deferred)
- Add TTL/versioning to the session cache (single-run CLI, unnecessary)
- Decouple topology from volatile data (design-epoch change, evaluate in Phase C)
- Touch `apy_base` or `apy_reward` on enriched nodes

### Note for Phase C

The `extra["pendle"]` namespace pattern should become the convention for all adapters. When Phase C promotes fields like `liquidity_usd` and `expiry` to first-class Node fields, evaluate whether an observation layer (sidecar snapshot index keyed by node id + timestamp) is a better home for volatile market data than inline node mutation. Phase B intentionally does not solve this — it uses the existing `extra` dict pattern and keeps the scope tight.

